metadata.name: Order and Disorder #8
metadata.description:
A quiet and contemplative response to the pandemic and the attempts by governments to control people and viruses. This piece channels both the fluid drip painting style of Jackson Pollock with order hidden in disorder, and the suprematist work of Kazimir Malevich, with order vainly imposed through symbols. Press "s" on the keyboard to save an image at 1500 x 2427 pixels. Each generation takes around 10 seconds to produce.

Made with p5.js

metadata.name: Games: Gem Puzzle #9
metadata.description:
This is a generative homage to the gem puzzle, said to be invented by Noyes Palmer Chapman in 1874. It's also known as the boss puzzle, 8 puzzle and 15 puzzle (depending on the number of pieces).

Click on a piece of the puzzle to move it to the empty space. To solve the puzzle, you must get all of the pieces in numerical order from top left to bottom right. 

To scramble the puzzle, type "s", and to reverse the scrambling (solving the puzzle), type "r". If you type a number x from 1 to 9, you will get a gem puzzle with x by x pieces. Type "n" to toggle the piece numbers showing.

metadata.name: Ripple / Cymatic #68
metadata.description:
Mathematical animations inspired by cymatics.  

Symmetric waves ripple around a boundary, causing infinitely complex patterns that evolve forever but never repeat.

Variations are the frequencies and amplitudes of waves, the boundary shape, and the velocity of phase shifts.

Some are contained, others escape to infinity.
